= Weekly Win Card = Weekly Scorecard
‚Äï
1. Spend the first 15 or 20 minutes at the beginning of each week to reflect on your progress from the past week and gather insights to improve this week.
2. Define what a "win" looks like for the week ahead with 3-5 big picture goals.
3. Translate each weekly goal into smaller, actionable tasks throughout the week.
4. Keep your plan dynamic and realistic‚ÄïAdd/adjust action items during the week. Reassess priorities midweek if needed.
5. Measure progress, not results‚ÄïFocus on consistency of action over outcome. Score yourself on execution rate: What % of planned tasks have been done?
6. Wrap up your week and prepare for the next‚Äï(1) Roll over important tasks to the next week. (2) Drop or delete anything that no longer matters.
